Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pot. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @Green Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small chunks.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

Drain and rinse the @Red Kidney Beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%g} and pepper chunks and cook, stirring, for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @Worcester Sauce{7.5%g} to the pan. Cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Finely Chopped Tomatoes with Basil{1%carton}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and kidney beans.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Soured Cream{75%g} into a small #bowl{}.

Add a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well.

Stir the @Baby Spinach{100%g} into the stew a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chorizo stew, a dollop of soured cream and a sprinkling of cheese. Enjoy!